                            <comment id="16910478" author="ijuma" created="Mon, 19 Aug 2019 15:19:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rsivaram&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rsivaram&quot;&gt;rsivaram&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=omkreddy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;omkreddy&quot;&gt;omkreddy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16912437" author="omkreddy" created="Wed, 21 Aug 2019 15:50:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In case of SASL/Kerberos, client should know fully-qualified host name of the server and must match with hostname in principal. So we may need to do DNS lookup to find-out hostname of server IP.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;hostname is used to build&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/network/SaslChannelBuilder.java#L203&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;SaslClientAuthenticator&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/com&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;SslTransportLayer&lt;/a&gt; . We can avoid the lookup while building underlyting SslTransportLayer instance.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16916481" author="rsivaram" created="Tue, 27 Aug 2019 07:47:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-7188&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-7188&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
